<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Let's suppose we use this URL /module/controller/action/param1/1/param2/2</p>

<p>If I call $this-&gt;_getAllParams() in my controller I get an array off five parameters.
Now imagine I only want user parameters (ie param1 and param2) but I can't predict
their name. I must call _getAllParams() and unset the keys corresponding to the
module, controller and action. I must add logic in my application that is dependant of
the internal logic of the zend MVC. Yes I could do an controller helper but I'm not sure
this is the right way as the functionnality could be need by other peoples.</p>

<p>It would be great if we could just call an _getAllUserParams() that will return all params
except module+controller+action.</p>

